The initial configuration, THE160ASP160Face001.gro, was constructed from the experimental crystal structure and used as the starting point for all simulations. System preparation followed the procedure outlined below.

1. Energy minimization:
Steepest descent energy minimization was performed using the gromacs-energy-minimization.mdp parameter file.

2. NVT equilibration:
The system was equilibrated for 750 ps with a 2 fs time step at a target temperature of 298 K using the gromacs-nvt-equilibration-md-parameters-base.mdp file.

3. NPT equilibration:
Anisotropic Parrinello–Rahman pressure coupling at 1 bar was applied through three consecutive equilibration stages with time steps of 0.1 fs (100 ns), 0.2 fs (3.5 ns), and 0.4 fs (2.5 ns).

4. NPT production:
A 25 ns production simulation was carried out under NPT conditions at 1 bar using the Parrinello–Rahman barostat with a 0.2 fs time step.

The parameter file gromacs-npt-md-parameters-base.mdp was adapted as needed for both the NPT equilibration (step 3) and NPT production (step 4) simulations.
